TITLE: Traffic Signals
CASECLOSUREREASONDESCRIPTION: Sorry this probably isnâ€™t the appropriate category, please forward to the appropriate department. At W Kearney St and 76th heading east on Kearney, there is no signage stating showing which direction you can go from each lane (e.g. left turn only, straight/left turn etc). There has never been signage here and it seems completely obvious to me, however, for some reason for the last few months, maybe once a week I will encounter a driver who thinks you can turn left from either lane. The left lane has the option to go straight, so you can see why this could be an issue if the left lane decides to go straight and the right lane decides to turn left. It makes no sense to me, maybe people are just becoming less intelligent. Itâ€™s never been an issue in the 5 years Iâ€™ve lived here but itâ€™s frequent now for whatever reason. We may need to adapt to the decline in driving skills and install signs or paint arrows on the road. In case itâ€™s relevant, it does not seem to matter whether or not there are other several vehicles waiting at the light or not. Iâ€™ve seen it happen in heavy traffic and when I was alone with 1 other vehicle at the light.
